            </rs>.</p>
               <p>JOHN COHEN. I am a <rs id="t18280221-267-viclabel1417" type="occupation">musician</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18280221-267-victim1512 t18280221-267-viclabel1417"></join>, and live in <placeName id="t18280221-267-crimeloc1418">Leman-street, Goodman's-fields</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18280221-267-crimeloc1418" type="placeName" value="Leman-street, Goodman's-fields"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18280221-267-crimeloc1418" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18280221-267-off1415 t18280221-267-crimeloc1418"></join>; the prisoner was about four weeks in my employ. On the 20th of January I missed a sovereign, and on the 25th some money was marked; the prisoner behaved very well before this - the half-sovereign was taken on the 26th - he behaved very honest before.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18280221-267-person1513">
                  JOHN 
                  BRENDLING
               <interp inst="t18280221-267-person1513" type="surname" value="BRENDLING"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280221-267-person1513" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280221-267-person1513" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am landlord of the house where Cohen lives. I marked eleven sovereigns and a half-sovereign for him; he put them into a bag, and gave them to his wife; the prisoner was charged with taking a half-sovereign, and gave it up to me; here it is - it is the one I marked.</p>

               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18280221-267-person1514">
                  MARY 
                  COHEN
               <interp inst="t18280221-267-person1514" type="surname" value="COHEN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280221-267-person1514" type="given" value="MARY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280221-267-person1514" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . On Saturday Brendling marked some sovereigns, in a bag, which I put into a box, in my bed-room, and locked it; on Sunday morning my husband told me half a sovereign was missing.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18280221-267-person1515">
                  JAMES 
                  LEE
               <interp inst="t18280221-267-person1515" type="surname" value="LEE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280221-267-person1515" type="given" value="JAMES"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280221-267-person1515" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I apprehended the prisoner on the 26th; I made him no promise; I said, "Where is the half-sovereign?" he said he had taken it out of the box, and given it to Brendling before I got there.</p>
               <p>GUILTY. Aged 14.</p>
